From vobencha at fredhutch.org  Thu Jun 11 17:51:55 2015
From: vobencha at fredhutch.org (Valerie Obenchain)
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2015 08:51:55 -0700
Subject: [Bioc-devel] strandless introns with
	VariantAnnotation::locateVariants()
In-Reply-To: <5579623C.8000703@upf.edu>
References: <42378_1433868294_55771806_42378_3084_19_557717DE.8090502@upf.edu>
	<5578CE79.6020004@fredhutch.org> <5579623C.8000703@upf.edu>
Message-ID: <5579AE9B.7020401@fredhutch.org>

This issue is that 'subject' is a GRangesList which has multiple strands 
per list element (so a simple strand(subject) can't be used to construct 
a GRanges). Additionally, there could be different strands in a single 
list element. I've added a check for this and a warning is thrown and 
strand is set to '*' if different strands are found in the same list 
element.

The fix has been checked into release and devel.

Valerie


